
[1]coloquintida

   COLOQUINTIDA, n. The colocynth or bitter apple, the fruit of a plant of
   the genus Cucumis, a native of Syria and of Crete. It is of the size of
   a large orange, containing a pulp which is violently purgative, but
   sometimes useful as a medicine.
